    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNow that neovim 10 supports pull diagnostics, I think it'd be useful to expose some additional flags to control how often diagnostic requests are sent.\r\n\r\nRight now, diagnostics are requested after each `didChange` event, which can be controlled partially via existing lsp client flags like `debounce_text_changes`: https://neovim.io/doc/user/lsp.html#_lua-module:-vim.lsp.client\r\n\r\nSome lsp servers like eslint expose options to run diagnostics on save, since they can be a little slow. [With pull diagnostics, those settings have to be on the client-side to function](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/issues/3211).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo start, I propose adding a new flag `pull_diagnostics_on_save` that sends diagnostic requests after `didSave` instead of `didChange` for that lsp client.\r\n\r\nAny thoughts or concerns? I'm happy to try implementing if it sounds like a reasonable idea!",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
