            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Has there been any progress on this one? I recently started using ruff via https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/ruff.lua and the diagnostics are often delayed several seconds because of my setting `debounce_text_changes = 5000`. (Note that one has to either disable `semantic_tokens` and `document_color` or apply [a workaround](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39785#issuecomment-4450886150) for `debounce_text_changes` to actually debounce)\n\npylsp isn't affected by this because nvim sends `didSave` to it, but no `didSave` is being sent to ruff (only the debounced `didChange`) and diagnostics are only being pulled after the debounced `didChange`.\n\nIs there any way I can force a `didChange`/`didSave` to be sent when the buffer is saved?",
