            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Actually, I figured it out myself (it was extra annoying indeed so I had to lol):\n\n```lua\n-- force sending didChange on save to servers that don't ask for didSave\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('BufWritePost', {\n\tgroup = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup('DidChangeFlush', {}),\n\tcallback = function(ev)\n\t\tfor _, client in pairs(vim.lsp.get_clients({ bufnr = ev.buf })) do\n\t\t\trequire(\"vim.lsp._changetracking\").flush(client, ev.buf)\n\t\tend\n\tend,\n})\n```\n\nIt's clearly a hack as `vim.lsp._changetracking` isn't public API but it seems to work with both 0.11 and 0.12 so that's good for now.",
            "created_at": "2026-05-14T13:43:56Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/29792#issuecomment-4451214612",
            "id": 4451214612,
