        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Some extra context…\n\ndidSave autocmd: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6780e78b0981f52aec9c4ef96356d3fef3742c9a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua#L939-L946\n\ndidSave impl that only sends didSave if the server asked for it: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6780e78b0981f52aec9c4ef96356d3fef3742c9a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_changetracking.lua#L207-L219\n\nhow the didChange happens before the didSave: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6780e78b0981f52aec9c4ef96356d3fef3742c9a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua#L851-L854\n\nMy autocmd simply unconditionally calls `flush` always to make sure `didChange` gets sent on save regardless of whether `didSave` got sent or not. Seems to me this might be a good thing to do anyway? Shall I open a PR?",
