            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> My autocmd simply unconditionally calls `flush` always to make sure `didChange` gets sent on save regardless of whether `didSave` got sent or not. Seems to me this might be a good thing to do anyway? Shall I open a PR?\n\nSomething like this might do:\n\n```diff\ndiff --git ./runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_changetracking.lua ./runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_changetracking.lua\nindex 0788cd186d..a8cbcf856c 100644\n--- ./runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_changetracking.lua\n+++ ./runtime/lua/vim/lsp/_changetracking.lua\n@@ -216,6 +216,8 @@ function M._send_did_save(bufnr)\n           },\n           text = included_text,\n         })\n+      else\n+        M.flush(client, bufnr)\n       end\n     end\n   end\n```",
